-30 and 9-45-31, it may be provided in and by the resolution determining the necessity of any street improvement that the cost thereof shall be assessed against all assessable lots and tracts each lot and tract of land fronting or abutting thereon or lying within one-half block or three hundred feet thereof, whichever is less, according to the benefits determined by the governing body to accrue to each of such lots and tracts lot and tract from the construction of the improvement. In such event the The governing body, in preparing, considering, and hearing objections to the assessment roll as provided in chapter 9-43, shall make such an investigation as may be necessary and shall find and determine the amount in which each such lot and tract will be especially is specifically benefited by the construction of the improvement, and shall assess against each such lot and tract such the amount, not exceeding said the benefit as shall be necessary to pay its just portion of the total cost of the work to be assessed. 500 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.021 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 15461, "bill_version_id": 86219, "bill_version": "House State Affairs Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-09T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to permit assessments based on benefits. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That \u00a7 9-45-32 be amended to read as follows: 9-45-32. In lieu of the method of apportionment prescribed in \u00a7 \u00a7 9-45-30 and 9-45-31, it may be provided in and by the resolution determining the necessity of any street improvement that the cost thereof shall be assessed against all assessable lots and tracts each lot and tract of land fronting or abutting thereon or lying within one-half block or three hundred feet thereof, whichever is less, according to the benefits determined by the governing body to accrue to each of such lots and tracts lot and tract from the construction of the improvement. In such event the The governing body, in preparing, considering, and hearing objections to the assessment roll as provided in chapter 9-43, shall make such an investigation as may be necessary and shall find and determine the amount in which each such lot and tract will be especially is specifically benefited by the construction of the improvement, and shall assess against each such lot and tract such the amount, not exceeding said the benefit as shall be necessary to pay its just portion of the total cost of the work to be assessed. No payment may be made by the state on any assessment against state property except in accordance with \u00a7 5-14-19. BILL HISTORY 1/15/00 First read in House and referred to State Affairs. H.J. 54 2/9/00 Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date. 2/9/00 State Affairs Do Pass Amended, Passed, AYES 13, NAYS 0."}, {"bill_id": 15461, "bill_version_id": 86218, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2000-02-22T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 15461, "action_date": "2000-01-15T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85628, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85628.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 54, "committee_id_action": 656, "committee_id_assigned": 651, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15461, "action_date": "2000-02-09T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85895, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/85895.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for Committee hearing on this date", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 651, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 15461, "action_date": "2000-02-09T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 85895, "document_url":